<figureCitation box="[284,404,1933,1959]" captionStart="FIGURE 2-2" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1649,1673]" captionTargetBox="[226,1301,182,1625]" captionTargetId="figure-27@8.[151,1436,181,1625]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 2-2. Adiscus daofuensis Duan &amp; Zhou, sp. nov.:A. epipleural lobe of elytra; B. prosternum; C. spermatheca; D. lateral view of aedeagus; E. dorsal view of aedeagus; F. ventral view of aedeagus. (Scale bars: A–B = 0.5 mm, C–F = 0.2 mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6036404" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6036404/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Fig. 2-1A</figureCitation>
) short, broadly ovate, almost rectangular; dorsum smooth, mostly yellowish brown. Antennomeres 1-5 yellow, 6-11 brown; labrum and mandibles black. Pronotum with basal margin black. Legs and venter yellowish brown.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6036397" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6036397" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6036397/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" startId="7.[151,250,1828,1852]" targetBox="[182,1402,186,1782]" targetPageId="7">
