<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,297,1828,1852]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">FIGURE 2-1.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[306,491,1828,1852]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Adiscus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="daofuensi">
<emphasis box="[306,491,1828,1852]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Adiscus daofuensi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
s Duan &amp; Zhou, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[667,749,1829,1853]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[667,749,1829,1853]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
: A. habitus; B. lateral view of habitus; C. ventral view of habitus; D. head; E. antennae; F. spermatheca; G. rectal pad; H. lateral view of aedeagus; I. dorsal view of aedeagus; J. ventral view of aedeagus. (Scale bars: A–D = 0.5 mm, E–J = 0.2 mm).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6036404" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6036404" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6036404/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" startId="8.[151,250,1649,1673]" targetBox="[226,1301,182,1625]" targetPageId="8">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,1649,1709]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,295,1649,1673]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">FIGURE 2-2.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Duan &amp; Zhou" authorityName="Duan &amp; Zhou" authorityYear="2022" box="[300,639,1649,1673]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Adiscus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="daofuensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[300,492,1649,1673]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Adiscus daofuensis</emphasis>
Duan &amp; Zhou
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[648,727,1649,1673]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[648,727,1649,1673]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
: A. epipleural lobe of elytra; B. prosternum; C. spermatheca; D. lateral view of aedeagus; E. dorsal view of aedeagus; F. ventral view of aedeagus. (Scale bars: A–B = 0.5 mm, C–F = 0.2 mm).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1755,2034]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
Head (
<figureCitation box="[275,387,1755,1782]" captionStart="FIGURE 2-2" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1649,1673]" captionTargetBox="[226,1301,182,1625]" captionTargetId="figure-27@8.[151,1436,181,1625]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 2-2. Adiscus daofuensis Duan &amp; Zhou, sp. nov.:A. epipleural lobe of elytra; B. prosternum; C. spermatheca; D. lateral view of aedeagus; E. dorsal view of aedeagus; F. ventral view of aedeagus. (Scale bars: A–B = 0.5 mm, C–F = 0.2 mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6036404" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6036404/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Fig. 2-1D</figureCitation>
) nearly round; distinctly and sparsely punctate. Eyes reniform; superior eye-lobes separated by slightly greater distance than antennal insertions. Clypeus finely and transversely wrinkled, anterior margin arcuately emarginated. Antennae (
<figureCitation box="[536,644,1827,1854]" captionStart="FIGURE 2-2" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1649,1673]" captionTargetBox="[226,1301,182,1625]" captionTargetId="figure-27@8.[151,1436,181,1625]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 2-2. Adiscus daofuensis Duan &amp; Zhou, sp. nov.:A. epipleural lobe of elytra; B. prosternum; C. spermatheca; D. lateral view of aedeagus; E. dorsal view of aedeagus; F. ventral view of aedeagus. (Scale bars: A–B = 0.5 mm, C–F = 0.2 mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6036404" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6036404/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Fig. 2-1E</figureCitation>
) reaching elytral humeri, scape clubbed, pedicel oblong, about half as long as scape, antennomeres 3–5 slender, 3 
<superScript attach="left" box="[644,658,1863,1877]" fontSize="6" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">rd</superScript>
as long as pedicel, 4 
<superScript attach="left" box="[899,912,1863,1877]" fontSize="6" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">th</superScript>
as long as 5 
<superScript attach="none" box="[1056,1069,1863,1877]" fontSize="6" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">th</superScript>
, 6–11 somewhat broadened and flattened, last pointed apically.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1755,2034]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
Pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[326,436,1935,1962]" captionStart="FIGURE 2-2" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1649,1673]" captionTargetBox="[226,1301,182,1625]" captionTargetId="figure-27@8.[151,1436,181,1625]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 2-2. Adiscus daofuensis Duan &amp; Zhou, sp. nov.:A. epipleural lobe of elytra; B. prosternum; C. spermatheca; D. lateral view of aedeagus; E. dorsal view of aedeagus; F. ventral view of aedeagus. (Scale bars: A–B = 0.5 mm, C–F = 0.2 mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6036404" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6036404/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Fig. 2-1A</figureCitation>
) smooth, much broader basely than apically, basal width about twice as long as pronotal length. Anterior margin weakly arched. Posterior margin serrate and undulated, and produced into an obtuse angle of about 100° at middle. Disc evenly convex, impunctate. Posterior margin sinuate with fine serration.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,151,934]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
Elytra (
<figureCitation box="[287,402,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURE 2-2" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1649,1673]" captionTargetBox="[226,1301,182,1625]" captionTargetId="figure-27@8.[151,1436,181,1625]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 2-2. Adiscus daofuensis Duan &amp; Zhou, sp. nov.:A. epipleural lobe of elytra; B. prosternum; C. spermatheca; D. lateral view of aedeagus; E. dorsal view of aedeagus; F. ventral view of aedeagus. (Scale bars: A–B = 0.5 mm, C–F = 0.2 mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6036404" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6036404/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Fig. 2-1A</figureCitation>
) oblong, humeri somewhat prominent, widest slightly behind humeri, feebly rounded at sides and apex. Disc sparsely and finely punctate, with 11 regular striae, intervals with scattered minute punctures. Epipleural lobe (
<figureCitation box="[337,447,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURE 2-2" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1649,1673]" captionTargetBox="[226,1301,182,1625]" captionTargetId="figure-27@8.[151,1436,181,1625]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 2-2. Adiscus daofuensis Duan &amp; Zhou, sp. nov.:A. epipleural lobe of elytra; B. prosternum; C. spermatheca; D. lateral view of aedeagus; E. dorsal view of aedeagus; F. ventral view of aedeagus. (Scale bars: A–B = 0.5 mm, C–F = 0.2 mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6036404" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6036404/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Fig. 2-2A</figureCitation>
) moderately large, lateral margins slightly expanded ventrally with rounded lobe at basal 1/3 of elytron, with both lobe sides forming angle of 130°; epipleura obliquely placed and visible in lateral view.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,151,934]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
Venter (
<figureCitation box="[289,399,295,321]" captionStart="FIGURE 2-2" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1649,1673]" captionTargetBox="[226,1301,182,1625]" captionTargetId="figure-27@8.[151,1436,181,1625]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 2-2. Adiscus daofuensis Duan &amp; Zhou, sp. nov.:A. epipleural lobe of elytra; B. prosternum; C. spermatheca; D. lateral view of aedeagus; E. dorsal view of aedeagus; F. ventral view of aedeagus. (Scale bars: A–B = 0.5 mm, C–F = 0.2 mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6036404" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6036404/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Fig. 2-1C</figureCitation>
) clothed with short pubescence and punctures. Prosternum (
<figureCitation box="[1083,1193,295,321]" captionStart="FIGURE 2-2" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1649,1673]" captionTargetBox="[226,1301,182,1625]" captionTargetId="figure-27@8.[151,1436,181,1625]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 2-2. Adiscus daofuensis Duan &amp; Zhou, sp. nov.:A. epipleural lobe of elytra; B. prosternum; C. spermatheca; D. lateral view of aedeagus; E. dorsal view of aedeagus; F. ventral view of aedeagus. (Scale bars: A–B = 0.5 mm, C–F = 0.2 mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6036404" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6036404/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Fig. 2-2B</figureCitation>
) trapezoidal, anterior margin not protruding, posterior margin nearly straight, central ridge absent, lateral ridges elevated. Mesoventrite broad, twice as wide as long. Metaventrite with dense coarse punctures. Pygidium with dense punctures and short pubescence.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,151,934]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,438,464]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Aedeagus.</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[338,590,439,465]" captionStart="FIGURE 2-2" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1649,1673]" captionTargetBox="[226,1301,182,1625]" captionTargetId="figure-27@8.[151,1436,181,1625]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 2-2. Adiscus daofuensis Duan &amp; Zhou, sp. nov.:A. epipleural lobe of elytra; B. prosternum; C. spermatheca; D. lateral view of aedeagus; E. dorsal view of aedeagus; F. ventral view of aedeagus. (Scale bars: A–B = 0.5 mm, C–F = 0.2 mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6036404" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6036404/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Figs. 2-1H–J; 2-2D–F</figureCitation>
) Median lobe elongate, about twice as long as wide, nearly parallel-sided. Apex of median lobe slightly narrower than middle, acute at apex, moderately curved in lateral view; each side of apex and the middle region of ventrally-dilated part with long setae; sparsely punctate on ventral side of distal part. Median orifice with median sclerite bending inwards above surface. Inner sac rather broad, lantern-shaped, dilated at middle, posterior margin nearly straight. Tegmen Y-shaped, weakly sclerotized, almost translucent.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,151,934]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,293,619,645]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Female.</emphasis>
Body more robust than male, apical hollow in ventrite 5 deep and round. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1137,1294,618,644]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Spermatheca</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 2-2" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1649,1673]" captionTargetBox="[226,1301,182,1625]" captionTargetId="figure-27@8.[151,1436,181,1625]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 2-2. Adiscus daofuensis Duan &amp; Zhou, sp. nov.:A. epipleural lobe of elytra; B. prosternum; C. spermatheca; D. lateral view of aedeagus; E. dorsal view of aedeagus; F. ventral view of aedeagus. (Scale bars: A–B = 0.5 mm, C–F = 0.2 mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6036404" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6036404/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Figs. 2-1F; 2-2C</figureCitation>
) falcate, acute-angled bending at apex 2/3, moderately acute at apex, slightly dilated at 1/3 from base, then become narrower; duct weakly sclerotized, irregularly coiled. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[846,1025,690,717]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Rectal sclerites</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[1041,1151,691,717]" captionStart="FIGURE 2-2" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1649,1673]" captionTargetBox="[226,1301,182,1625]" captionTargetId="figure-27@8.[151,1436,181,1625]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 2-2. Adiscus daofuensis Duan &amp; Zhou, sp. nov.:A. epipleural lobe of elytra; B. prosternum; C. spermatheca; D. lateral view of aedeagus; E. dorsal view of aedeagus; F. ventral view of aedeagus. (Scale bars: A–B = 0.5 mm, C–F = 0.2 mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6036404" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6036404/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Fig. 2-1G</figureCitation>
) strongly sclerotized, not connected between two rectangular sclerites on ventral side.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
